The paper deals with ontology debugging, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and knowledge representation (cs.LG). It also involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with debugging faulty ontologies. The paper proposes query selection strategies, which involve querying an oracle, making it relevant to databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (cs.CL) as it discusses the challenges of formulating and understanding logical descriptions.
